cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.IR

This paper discusses the challenges and advancements in detecting disinformation and fake news on social media, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also touches upon social media analysis, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society). Additionally, the paper discusses the ethical implications of disinformation and fake news, which could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
